{"id":23575,"title":"Sacroiliitis secondary to catheter-related bacteremia due to Mycobacterium abscessus (sensu stricto).","abstract":"We describe a case of sacroiliitis secondary to catheter-related bacteremia due to Mycobacterium abscessus (sensu stricto). This case confirms that MultiLocus sequence typing and variable-number tandem-repeat methods are very robust techniques to identify the pathogen species and to validate molecular epidemiological links among complex M. abscessus isolates. ","date":"2014-03-06","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24479655","annotations":[{"name":"Pathogen","weight":0.621095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogen"},{"name":"Molecule","weight":0.268449,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecule"},{"name":"Epidemiology","weight":0.262604,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemiology"},{"name":"Species","weight":0.256056,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Species"},{"name":"Mycobacterium","weight":0.231059,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mycobacterium"},{"name":"Nucleic acid sequence","weight":0.150637,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nucleic_acid_sequence"},{"name":"Bacteremia","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacteremia"},{"name":"Sacroiliitis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sacroiliitis"},{"name":"Mycobacterium abscessus","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mycobacterium_abscessus"},{"name":"Sensu","weight":0.0290048,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sensu"},{"name":"Coordination complex","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coordination_complex"},{"name":"Typing","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typing"},{"name":"Primary isolate","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"htt